HEADWORD: Oso-berry
<hw>O"so-ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The small, blueblack, drupelike fruit of the <spn>Nuttallia
cerasiformis</spn>, a shrub of Oregon and California, belonging to the
Cherry tribe of <fam>Rosaceae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

